cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about object detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel approach to object detection, which involves detecting objects as paired keypoints, and introduces a new type of pooling layer, which could be considered as a contribution to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents experimental results and compares its approach to existing methods, which could be seen as a contribution to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on object detection could also make it relevant to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of neural networks and the optimization of performance could also make this paper relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
